README for mplabalc30

REQUIREMENTS

   Download the MPLAB X IDE from
   - http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/MPLABX-v1_30-linux-installer.run

   Download the MPLAB XC32 from
   - http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/xc32-v1.00-linux.zip

   Download the MPLAB XC16 from
   - http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/xc16-v1_00-linux-installer.run

   Above installers require JAVA 1.6:
      Install JAVA 1.6 to some location
         export jdkhome to that location before running the
         above installers
      export jdkhome=/tmp/jre1.6.0_35/

   The above installers create a v1.00 directory in the installed
      directory. Do the below from the parent directory of v1.00
      directory.

      mkdir pic30-v1.00
      cd pic30-v1.00
      mkdir -p bin/device_files
      cp -r ../v1.00/bin/device_files bin/
      cp ../v1.00/bin/c30_device.info bin/
      cp -r ../v1.00/support ./
      find . -type f -exec dos2unix {} \;
      cd ..
      tar cvf pic30-v1.00.tar pic30-v1.00
      gzip pic30-v1.00.tar

   and put the file
   - pic30-v1.00.tar.gz

   into the directory defined by PKGMK_SOURCE_DIR. See pkgmk.conf(5).
